   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The patch here needs some work, but it's getting there. Here's what I think needs 
being changed:

* You use em dashes, rather than hyphens, in the "git config --global" parts of the 
docs. It seems that that is live right now, so I realize I should have caught those 
earlier, but these commits should really fix that. (If you don't see what I mean, 
try copy-pasting what you said.)

* A default email address should be <a href="mailto:me@example.com">me@example.com</a> (example.com is actually 
reserved for this use; see <a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2606.txt">http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2606.txt</a> )
 the "next" link 

* I would prefer, slightly, that we actually validate that the user has configured 
things in a reasonable way. Like asking them to paste the output of 'git config --
global user.email' and making sure it has an @ sign in it. But I guess if we make 
the experience super clear, we don't *have* to do that.

Those are my thoughts; let me know if I missed something.</pre>
